          "description": "Jocelyn was my PA and was absolutely excellent.\n\nHowever, the front desk staff and nurses I found to be sweet, but incredibly unprofessional. There was deli coffee just sitting on the table of my exam room, the nurses were sweet but seemed very disinterested in being there. It felt like highschoolers who just had to do their job.\nThe woman who I dealt with (who told me she\u2019s the office manager) was very dismissive and had a negative attitude on the phone. I was trying to refill my prescription and asked me \u201cwhy didn\u2019t you schedule a follow-up?\u201d\nAs a patient, I am expecting basic courtesy and help in resolving medical issues; not judgement and blatant disinterest in helping me.\n\nFurthermore, the office never called me back for blood results (I had to call them.)\nI feel bad because the PA was very attentive, but the staff makes me want to find a new office.",
